A few thoughts:

- There can be binary BC concerns for existing 0.1.x pulsar users. However I think the new interface enforces type information and can easily support existing producers with an identical codec: `byte[] -> byte[]`. It might be worthing breaking binary BC for 0.2.x pulsar releases.

- I think `PulsarClient` doesn't have to be typed. The type information is associated with topics, and can be enforced at Producers and Consumers. You can do followings:

```
public interface PulsarClient {

<T> Producer<T> createProducer(..., Codec<T> codec);

<T> Consumer<T> createConsumer(..., Codec<T> codec);

}
```

- I think `Codec<T>` can be more gc-friendly with ByteBuf and InputStream.

```
public interface Codec<T> {

byte[] encode(T value);

T decode(byte[] bytes);

ByteBuf encodeBuf(T value);

T decodeBuf(ByteBuf buffer);

void encode(T value, OutputStream os);

T decode(InputStream is);

}
```

